This store is terribly managed and they are so rude. My boyfriend and I placed an order online and it said it would be ready in 20 mins, when we arrived at the time it was suppose to be ready the order wasn't there, my boyfriend asked where it was, she rudely said someone already took that order. We were confused as we just got there at the time we were suppose to, so we asked her to make the food again she refused and said we would have to pay AGAIN. Mind you we work in the loop and order pick ups often from all over, this has never happened. She continued to yell and say she doesn't have time to talk to us because she is busy. I couldn't even believe how she was acting while we still have no food that we already paid for. She was at fault and then on top of that yelling at us? We left we don't need to be disrespected by someone who we are paying for something, we disputed the charge thru the bank but this store's staff including the manager needs a politeness refresher and how to handle situations that they are at fault for.

Just got back from getting a regular #9 on wheat. First time visiting a Jersey Mike's and likely the last. First off, the guy making sandwiches must be new, because he was completely disorganized. Trying to make three people's sandwiches at once and almost messing up all of them if it weren't for the customers correcting him. The rest of the crew wasn't much better except for maybe the guy slicing meats and the cashier. And my sandwich is a mess with about a third of the ingredients falling out. That would be okay if it weren't mostly lettuce. I needed a fork to eat it (along with lots of napkins that didn't get put in the bag with the sandwich to go). The sandwich tastes fine, but I expected a sandwich that costs almost $10 to have bread that's better than Subway (which wouldn't be hard). But it isn't. I just have to maybe foolishly believe the small amount of meats are of better quality.

Ahoy! All ships set sail for bland!  Went here with three coworkers. I ordered the buffalo chicken wrap, others ordered what they think is a cheesesteak and another got a cold turkey sandwich.  The cold turkey won out as the only sandwich worth eating, and even then it only received mediocre praise as being "better than Subway". Beating Subway is like having pizza that ranks just above school lunchroom pizza product.  The cheesesteaks looked pretty weak. Too much bread, not enough meat, not enough cheese. It just barely passes for a steak sandwich at all.  My wrap was disappointing. It took 5 minutes longer to prepare than everyone else's, so you'd assume it was hot. No. It lacked heat in taste and temperature. Weak! For $6 and change, I'd expect a little more than some rubbery chicken bits with the weakest non-buffalo sauce ever splashed over it with conciliatory bits of lettuce. As Meghan O. pleads, please stop cutting wraps in half. It makes eating them messy and inconvenient.  I hate to bash the workers, because they all did look busy, but with an entire battalion of preppers working the counter, and no line to speak of, why service was so slow is beyond me.
